																								 New Delhi, Dec. 28: The finance ministry today clarified that investments in the five year post office deposit and senior citizens savings schemes on or after April 1, 2007, would be eligible for income tax benefit under Section 80C. The investment by an individual or a Hindu undivided family in these two instruments during the previous year 2007-08 (relevant to assessment year 2008-09), and subsequent years, shall be eligible for deduction under section 80C of the Income-tax Act, subject to the overall ceiling of Rs 1 lakh in that section, the statement said.
																								 Mumbai, Dec. 28: The Anil Ambani group today got the regulatory go-ahead from Sebi for the public issue of Reliance Power Ltd (RPL)  the groups first IPO that is estimated to raise $3 billion.
																								 Mumbai, Dec. 28: Indias foreign exchange reserves dipped $232 million for the week ended December 21 to $272.722 billion. 
																								 Mumbai, Dec. 28: The Reserve Bank, in a move to impose greater financial discipline, today asked all regional rural banks to disclose capital-to-risk-weighted- assets ratios for 2007-08.
																								 Mumbai, Dec. 28: The JSW Steel board has approved a proposal to set up a joint venture plant at Rustavi in Georgia at an estimated project cost of $42 million (Rs 165.35 crore).

